    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Mapping CO (5-4) in BAND 6</prj:name>
        <prj:note>This science goal is designed to detect and resolve in different spatial elements (0.2 arcsec angular resolution) the CO(5-4) line emission redshifted in Band 6, for a Compton-thick QSO at z=1.245.

We propose observations of CO(5-4) line since it represents a reasonable compromise between the following factors:
1) this CO transitions has been already observed in the literature (Carilli et al. 2001; Papadoupoulos et al. 2010) in quasar host galaxies.
2) Assuming the most conservative CO SLED among those calibrated on active star-forming galaxies, the CO(5-4) transition turns to be more than 10 times brighter than the CO(1-0).
3) The Band 6 is weakly affected by atmospheric opacity with respect to Bands 7, 8 or 9.
</prj:note>
